      <strong>Summary</strong>
    </p>
    <p xmlns="">EDITORIAL REVIEW: **The *New York Times* bestselling
    novel.** This is the riveting first-person narrative of Kvothe,
    a young man who grows to be one of the most notorious magicians
    his world has ever seen. From his childhood in a troupe of
    traveling players, to years spent as a near-feral orphan in a
    crime-riddled city, to his daringly brazen yet successful bid
    to enter a legendary school of magic, *The Name of the Wind* is
    a masterpiece that transports readers into the body and mind of
    a wizard.</p>
